# Core Explanations

## What is Artificial Intelligence (AI)?

Imagine you ask Google Maps to find the fastest route to your house.
The computer has to think like a human — it looks at traffic, roads, and time.
When a **computer can do a task that normally needs human thinking**, we call that **Artificial Intelligence (AI)**.

AI is a very big umbrella. It includes many different areas — not only machine learning.
Think of AI as a large building, and machine learning is just one floor inside that building.

> 💡 **Easy Example:** A self-driving car uses AI to "see" the road. The part that helps it "see" uses something called Deep Learning — which is part of machine learning — which is part of AI.

---

## What is Machine Learning (ML)?

Machine Learning is when we use **statistics and algorithms** (mathematical rules) to let a computer **learn from data** and get better with more experience.

Instead of us writing every rule for the computer ("if it rains, slow down"), we give the computer lots of examples and it finds the rules **by itself**.

> 💡 **Easy Example:** You show a child 100 photos of cats and 100 photos of dogs. After seeing many examples, the child can tell the difference. Machine learning does the same thing — it learns from examples.

---

## What is Data Mining?

**Data Mining** is an older term that means **finding patterns and rules inside large amounts of data**.

Today in the industry, people use the terms "data mining" and "machine learning" almost interchangeably. You can think of them as the same thing for most purposes.

---

## What is Deep Learning?

**Deep Learning** is a special family of machine learning algorithms. It is especially good at:

- **Computer vision** (understanding images and photos)
- **Text analysis** (understanding written language)

Deep Learning is what powers things like image recognition on your phone and ChatGPT.

---

## Summary of Definitions

| Term | Simple Meaning |
|------|---------------|
| **Artificial Intelligence** | Computers doing human-like tasks |
| **Machine Learning** | Computers learning from data using statistics |
| **Data Mining** | Finding patterns in large data (same as ML, older term) |
| **Deep Learning** | Special ML algorithms for images and text |

> 📝 **Note to self:** Deep Learning ⊂ Machine Learning ⊂ Artificial Intelligence
> (Deep Learning is *inside* Machine Learning, which is *inside* AI)

