## Types of Machine Learning

There are three main types:

### Supervised Learning

The computer **learns from examples that already have the answer**.

- You give it data with **inputs (X)** and the **correct answer (Y)**.
- The computer finds the relationship between X and Y.
- Later, you give it new X, and it predicts Y.

> 💡 **Example:** You show 1,000 emails labelled "spam" or "not spam".
> The computer learns what makes an email spam.
> Then it can check new emails automatically.

There are two types of supervised learning:

| Type | What it predicts | Example |
|------|-----------------|---------|
| **Classification** | A category (yes/no, type A/B/C) | Will this customer leave? (Yes / No) |
| **Regression** | A number | What will the house price be? (€320,000) |

### Unsupervised Learning

The computer **finds patterns on its own — with no labels given**.

> 💡 **Example:** You give the computer 10,000 customer records with no labels.
> It groups customers into clusters by similarity.
> You discover there are 4 different types of customers.

### Reinforcement Learning

The computer **learns by trial and error** — like playing a video game.
It tries actions, gets a reward for good ones, and a penalty for bad ones.
Over time, it learns to make better decisions.

> 💡 **Example:** AlphaGo (the AI that plays the board game Go)
> learned by playing millions of games against itself.

